pr_body:
Closes #60 

### Description
I added an info logger as a service. And added info logging for some functions such as loading OBJ geometry, loading GLTF geometry, exporting the scene, info about the event and run etc.

### Usage
We can instantiate the info logger through the constructor or passing it to the called function if the constructor is not a viable option.
Then we just use `this.infoLogger.add(text: string)` to add what we want to display on the info panel.

### Screen Capture
Here is how it looks:
![info-panel](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/81230989-e50b8980-900b-11ea-92b2-08f872eb8c8d.gif)

pr_body:
Hi,

These are some of the improvements to geometries and the overall scene.

**What's Added:**
* Use glTF geometries for ATLAS
* Add option to glTF loader for scaling geometries
* Use the same side (DoubleSide/FrontSide) for geometries as given in the glTF file
* Improve geometries by updating materials and some other stuff
* Increase camera frustum near plane which fixes all of the shader bugs with normal geometries
* Add option for using a single directional light that follows the camera (a little improved performance)
* Add option for using four directional lights that illuminate the entire scene

**Screenshots:**

**Before:**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/84643461-4a11a380-af17-11ea-8d96-222129a50dad.png)

**After:**

pr_title: Selection of 3D object from collections info panel
pr_body:
Fixes #93 

Hi,

## Description
Updated the collections info panel so that selection in the scene will highlight the event data items in the collections info panel and users can also highlight or move to objects in the scene from the collections info panel.

## Added
* Highlight event data in collections info panel on selection of event object from the scene
* Highlight event data in the scene on selection of event data from the collections info panel
* Ability to highlight and move camera to object from the collections info panel
* Works for all event data including Tracks, Muons, Hits and Clusters
* Two different options "Move camera to object" and "Highlight object" for highlighting event data from collections info panel
* Some fixes to the collections info panel
* A combination of `Tube` and `Line` for better selection of Tracks (Fixes #73)
* Use yellow color for Tracks if the theme is dark (should I remove this or is it fine? [CODE](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-collections/src/app/services/loaders/objects/phoenix-objects.ts#L36))

## Screen Capture
![wip-collections-final](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/84781234-034ba880-b000-11ea-9dfc-fb0af9f51aee.gif)

pr_title: Dynamically get metadata for experiment info
pr_body:
Hi,

## Description
This adds dynamic metadata to display in the experiment info section.

## Added
* Get run number, event number and LS from event data
* Add support for optionally using an object with label and value (label is bold)
* Tagline for experiment

pr_body:
Closes #91 

Hi,

## Description

This adds CMS experiment support with ability to load an event from ".ig" archive files.

## Added

* Complete loader for CMS event data
* Support for Hits, Tracks, Jets, CaloClusters and MuonChambers physics objects
* Scaled CMS event data object geometry to fit Phoenix event display
* Support for all possible collections of the supported event data collection types
* Ability to read ".ig" files through the CMS loader
* An example of implementing custom physics objects (MuonChambers)
* Improved `PhoenixObjects`
  * Support for objects of Hits params in `PhoenixObjects` (previously support only an array of positions)
  * Improved Jets by limiting their length and checking their params for `et` / `energy` as possible energy params and using `theta` param if available
* Improved `PhoenixLoader`
  * Allowing to extend object types
  * Checking if collections are indeed objects so the collections info panel shows valid collections only

Misc
* Improved event meta data collection

## Screenshot

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/86125954-f1393200-baf6-11ea-8e9f-5c8ff88b30fc.png)

pr_body:
Closes #103 

Hi,

## Description

This makes the Jets scalable and also allows to extend UI menu options for each object type which can be used with any loader (by using the `PhoenixLoader.addObjectType` method from a child class).

I have been trying out options to scale Jets since yesterday but removing and recreating the Jets with increased energy wasn't working for large number of Jets. So after a lot of tries I came up with a minimal method which I think is the best.

## Added
* Fixed depthTest not working correctly
* Removed custom synchronous function to loop through children for changing depthTest (I am not sure why but `Object3D.traverse` seems to work now - while depthTest only worked with `updateChildrenDepthTest` function earlier)
* Made Jets scalable by increasing their scale and changing their position
* Ability to scale Jets from 1% to 200%
* Increased maximum Jet length to 3000 as it looks like a better option
* **Mechanism to add exclusive options to each event data type folder of dat.GUI through an optional callback passed to `PhoenixLoader.addObjectType`**

## Screen Capture
![wip-scalable-jets](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/86415564-e0e4ab00-bce0-11ea-8a97-af43b210c292.gif)

pr_title: New Phoenix Menu aka Experiment Controls
pr_body:
Hi,

## Description

This adds a brand new phoenix menu for controlling different data of the experiment including detector geometries and event data. It's hard to cover everything I did so here are the highlights of the final product. :)

## Added

* Phoenix menu component (`PhoenixMenuComponent`) taking in the root node for the phoenix menu
* Phoenix menu item (`PhoenixMenuItemComponent`) which is a single node inside phoenix menu component and can be extended to include children and config and the children can be further extended to include children and config
* Phoenix menu node (`PhoenixMenuNode`) which is the actual node as a class where children and configuration exist and other options like toggling of the phoenix menu node can be configured
* Created nodes as menu items and their children
* Support for optional slide toggle for each phoenix menu item
* Support for optional unique icons for each phoenix menu item
* Made custom configuration component for slider (also did for checkbox but that became redundant in a later iteration)
* Made `dat.GUI` menu optional and disabled by default (to enable, pass `true` to `Configuration` constructor or set `Configuration`'s `enableDatGUIMenu` property)
* Made all geometries and event data options available in phoenix menu by adding code in UI service
* Made phoenix menu optional (if no root node is set through configuration - the UI service will skip phoenix menu functions)
* Added phoenix menu to ATLAS and all other experiments replacing the dat.GUI menu (look good for all)
* Good architecture for easily extending and adding new options to phoenix menu
* Neat and consistent styling
* And a lot more

## Usage

The usage is simple. See [atlas.component.ts](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/sections/atlas/atlas.component.ts).

1. First we [create the root node](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/sections/atlas/atlas.component.ts#L16) 
1. Then we [set the phoenix menu root in the configuration](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/sections/atlas/atlas.component.ts#L29)
1. And then we just add the phoenix menu to the experiment section template like [this](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/sections/atlas/atlas.component.html#L5) specifying the root node as the one we created in step 1

### Possible Functions for a Phoenix Menu Node

See possible functions of `PhoenixMenuNode` in [phoenix-menu-node.ts](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/components/phoenix-menu/phoenix-menu-node/phoenix-menu-node.ts).

### Supported Configuration Types for Phoenix Menu Item

The configuration types that are currently supported are "label", "slider", "checkbox", "button" and "color". These can be seen in and extended from [this part of the code](https://github.com/9inpachi/phoenix/blob/wip-experiment-controls/src/app/components/phoenix-menu/pheonix-menu-item/phoenix-menu-item.component.html#L32-L55).

## Screen Capture

![wip-experiment-controls](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/87724718-5c605500-c7d5-11ea-8e33-72d5d311ad76.gif)

Hi,

## Description

This fixes a bug in which the phoenix menu geometries (Detector folder/node) were not repopulating when navigating from one experiment to another and back. The reason was that the phoenix menu was not properly re instantiated in the UI service.

## Added

* Proper clear operations for phoenix menu in UI service
* Redefining the phoenix menu root node for UI service
* Nullifying of phoenix menu nodes/folders for recreating them

pr_body:
Hi,

## Description

This adds JSROOT support to Phoenix with ability to load JSROOT scripts dynamically through a script loader, support for loading JSROOT's `.json.gz` and `.root` geometries and support for JSROOT event loader for loading event data from `.root` files.

Went through the JSROOT core code and edited the code (changed script paths) for proper integration. Deeply analyzed the JSROOT code including the `JSRootCore` and `JSRootPainter` and other files for getting and processing the event data from `.root` files.

## Added

* A generalized `ScriptLoader` for dynamically loading js script files without duplication
* Ability to dynamically load JSROOT script files through `ScriptLoader`
* Function for loading geometry object from `.root` and `.json.gz` files through the event display service
* A working JSROOT event loader
* Support for loading event data from `.root` file objects
* Loading multiple event data objects (tracks, hits etc.) from a `.root` file
* `JSRootEventLoader` for processing `.root` files to get `TEveTrack`s, `TGeoTrack`s and `TEvePointSet`s (Hits)
* Use ROOT JSON geometry for the CMS experiment (more detailed - **let me know if this is to be reverted back to the old geometry**)

Misc

* Don't sort track positions (`pos`) because it leads to weird behavior for extrapolated tracks whose curve might return back
* Fixed all the failing tests
* Add parameter for making the geometry's side DoubleSide with `loadJSONGeometry` function

## Usage (Example Code Snippets)

Loading `.json.gz` and `.root` geometries.

```ts
ScriptLoader.loadJSRootScripts((JSROOT: any) => {
  this.eventDisplay.loadRootJSONGeometry(JSROOT, 'https://root.cern/js/files/geom/cms.json.gz',
    'CMS Detector', 10, true);
  this.eventDisplay.loadRootGeometry(JSROOT, 'https://root.cern/js/files/geom/atlas2.root',
    'atlas', 'ATLAS Detector', 10, true);
});
```

Using `JSRootEventLoader`.

```ts
ScriptLoader.loadJSRootScripts((JSROOT: any) => {
  const jsrootEventLoader = new JSRootEventLoader(JSROOT, 'https://root.cern/js/files/geom/tracks_hits.root');
  jsrootEventLoader.getEventData(['tracks;1', 'hits;1'], (eventData: any) => {
    this.eventDisplay.buildEventDataFromJSON(eventData);
  });
});
```

## Screenshots

ROOT JSON geometry.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/89096241-9f821100-d3ee-11ea-825a-0c18095c2add.png)

JSROOT event loader's `TEveTrack`s.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/89096319-4797da00-d3ef-11ea-8daa-4753d94e7f29.png)

JSROOT event loader's `TEveTrack`s and `TEvePointSet`s (Hits).

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/89096383-bffe9b00-d3ef-11ea-85af-8c0f27143da1.png)

**Note:** @EdwardMoyse Can you please share a `.root` file with `TGeoTrack` objects? I couldn't find it in the JSROOT files [here](https://root.cern/js/files/).

This fixes major bugs and limitations of using Phoenix on mobile devices. Even some common functions like the UI menu were not working on mobile devices. Now Phoenix is complete usable on mobile devices.

* Made possible to hold zoom in and zoom out on mobile devices
* Improved overall object selection by optimizing code and making selection/highlighting more accurate
* Made object selection work on mobile devices (didn't work at all before)

## Screen Capture

pr_body:
Hi,

## Description

This adds options to animate event through clipping or extrapolating event data and option to animate camera translation through the scene. It also introduces some fixes.

## Added

* Function to animate camera through the scene by translating camera through a path
* Toggle to run camera animation
* Option to animate event by extrapolating tracks, scaling jets and using a bounding sphere for all other event objects
* Used and edited geometry of hits for animation with respect to the bounding sphere since multiple hits were a part of a single physics object
* Function to animate event using clipping planes in the form of a sphere
* Toggle to animate event objects propagation on collision (using clipping planes for animation - can be changed to the 1st method of event animation)
* Function to animate collision of two particles (basic - tried a lot to use `UnrealBloom` but skipped it)
* Use `BufferGeometry` for all physics objects (better performance)
* Created an `AnimationsManager` for all animation related functions
* Created an `EffectsManager` for managing post processing three.js effects (initially created for `UnrealBloom` - makes the code modular)

Misc

* Refactor code to use 2 spaces for tabs for consistency (some files were using 4 spaces)
* Fixed newly created tests
* Fixed #127 - Fixed duplicating options in phoenix menu in "Detector" config and enabled editing value of "Opacity" config
 
## Screen Capture

Tweening/translating camera through the scene

![wip-animations-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/91222223-4df04c00-e738-11ea-91c4-b6d1e3ae1352.gif)

---

Event animation using clipping planes
```
Eventdisplay.animateClippingWithCollision(duration: number, onEnd?: () => void)
```

![wip-animations-2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36920441/91222644-ea1a5300-e738-11ea-90d0-1af725c7ae7b.gif)

---

Event animation by extrapolating tracks, scaling jets and using a bounding sphere for all other event objects
```
Eventdisplay.animateEventWithCollision(duration: number, onEnd?: () => void)
```

pr_body:
Hi,

## Description

This adds complete VR support to Phoenix including fixing the already existing VR, making VR available for all experiments and adding ability to move inside the VR environment using the VR controller.

## Added

* Added VR to experiments with a custom toggle in UI menu which only shows for devices supporting VR
* Debugged and fixed VR not working showing scene on a single dimensional plane
* Created a VR manager for managing VR operations
* Option to open and close VR sessions through the VR toggle button
* Used a cloned camera and a separate minimal render function to work with VR (post-processing doesn't work)
* Ability to move inside the scene in the direction of camera using the VR controller
* Removed the "Playground VR" section since it became redundant

Misc

* Fixed SVG icons CSS in Collections Info's "Selection" column
* Updated three.js to r120 and fixed the bugs introduced
* Fixed bugs in phoenix menu
* Made the year in homepage section dynamic
* Basic tests for `AnimationsManager`
* Fixed tests and Travis

**TODO:** In the VR scene, the objects are not in order, I tried fixing it setting some scene properties and also using the renderer from `EffectComposer` (as it happens in normal mode) but it doesn't work.
@EdwardMoyse do you have any idea why this happens?

## Screen Capture
